definitions.definition: An island in San Francisco Bay California , United States , formerly the site of a famous prison ; in full, Alcatraz Island .
Ellipsis of Alcatraz Federal Penitentiary , a famous former U.S. federal prison, on the island .
Ellipsis of Fort Alcatraz , a U.S. coastal defense fort, predecessor of the prison .
